Disclosure of Stockpiles
An essential component of robust future nuclear arms reduction agreements will be the declaration of existing stockpiles of weapons and fissile materials to establish baseline data against which to measure future reductions. Without a declaration that specifies how many and what kind of nuclear materials are where, it will be difficult - if not impossible - to verify whether a country is complying with the agreed limitations.
To establish a meaningful baseline for reductions, this declaration should include the number of 
