an ultimate long-term advanced energy source for the country ... .14&#xD;
Even after the FY1996 changes, expressions of support continued. In the FY2000 DOE appropriations report, the House Committee on Appropriations stated, The Committee remains committed to a fusion program that is based on ... the ultimate goal of practical fusion energy.15&#xD;
During the 42-year span that witnessed substantial changes in budget levels, congressional support for a federally funded fusion energy R%26D effort and for its goal appears to have remained high. Over that period, Congress has noted also other benefits of the program such as advances in plasma science and engineering and the production of many highly trained scientists and engineers.&#xD;
